CBRE as the exclusive sales agents are pleased to present to you, Lots 21 & 22, 22 Darley Road, Manly.

The corner office suite comprised of two lots with an internal area of 175sqm* plus three secure car spaces.  Situated within the premier office strata building for Manly, the office suite situated on level three enjoys elevated views of water over Cabbage Tree Bay and views of Manly's Eastern Hill.

The suite provides a modern open planned fit-out, three partitioned meeting rooms and excellent natural light. The facilities include lift access, ducted air-conditioning, common toilets and an internal kitchenette. 

The property benefits from the following key attributes: 

- Two adjoining lots amalgamated into one office suite
- Total internal area of 175sqm* plus three secure car spaces
- Net passing income of $108,129 per annum* on a flexible lease
- Ideal for both investors and owner occupiers
- Situated within the premier office strata building in Manly
- Premium location just metres from Manly Corso, Beach and Wharf
- 15 minute* fast ferry to Sydney CBD

Lots 21 & 22, 22 Darley Road will be sold via public auction on Tuesday, 10 December 2019 at 10.30am

CBRE as the exclusive sales agents is pleased to present for the first time in 71 years 8 Belgrave Street, Manly.

Commanding a high-profile position, 8 Belgrave Street is a two storey freehold building comprising 4 shops on the ground floor and 4 office suites above, as well as basement storage.
Being located on one of the busiest streets in Manly, the property affords outstanding exposure. The ground floor of the building boasts an arcade, which pedestrians can use as a thoroughfare between Belgrave Street and Whistler Street Car Park (311 spaces). Large 12m* frontage to both Belgrave Street and Whistler Street provide significant street presence and signage opportunities (STCA). 8 Belgrave Street has a net lettable area of 491sqm*, with all of the suites currently leased, providing a passing net income of $153,562.43 per annum* with significant rental reversion opportunities.

Access to the property is possible via both Belgrave Street and Whistler Street, with the later entrance just 150m* from The Corso, one of Australia’s busiest and most desirable retail strips. The B2 Local Centre zoning, 3:1 floor space ratio and 15 metre height limit of the property also offers the potential for redevelopment (STCA). Located directly opposite the property at Gilbert Park are bus services that connect Manly to the greater Northern Beaches, Chatswood, North Sydney and Sydney CBD.

This property benefits from the following key attributes:

- First time offered to market in 71 years
- Multi-tenanted commercial freehold building
- High exposure with 2 street frontages
- Net Income: $152,959 p.a* with significant rental reversion opportunities 
- Moments from ferry service to Sydney CBD and bus services to greater Northern Beaches, Chatswood, North Sydney and Sydney CBD
- B2 Local Centre zoning, 3:1 FSR and 15m height limit allowing for development upside (STCA)

8 Belgrave Street, Manly will be sold via Auction on Tuesday, 1 June 2021 at 10:30am at AuctionWORKS (Online Bidding Available).

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate

For the first time in 37 years, CBRE as the exclusive sales agent is pleased to present to the market 47 The Corso, Manly. The property is a two storey multi-tenanted retail freehold situated at the heart of the Manly Corso Shopping Strip, named one of the most sought-after in the nation. The property capitalises on the eight million visitors a year that walk from the ferry wharf to the beach directly down the Corso. The ground floor is anchored by Platypus Shoes – Australia’s number one branded sneaker destination, owned by ASX Listed Accent Group (ASX:AX1). On the first floor is four office tenancies. The property is currently fully leased returning a net income of $169,742.24* per annum.

The property also provides many add value opportunities including activating the Market Place frontage and adding to the existing building which significantly underutilises the site (STCA). The suburb's access to public transport and major arterial roads allow for strong connectivity to Sydney's major commercial centres. Additionally, Manly wharf offers regular ferries that travel between Manly and the Sydney CBD.

47 The Corso, Manly benefits from the following key attributes:
•	Premium two-storey multi-tenanted retail freehold enjoying an exclusive location on the Manly Corso
•	High exposure investment with two street frontages
•	First time offered to market in 37 years
•       Anchored by ASX Listed Accent Group's Platypus Shoes
•	Underutilised site allows for the opportunity to add to the existing building (STCA)
•	Net Income: $169,742.24* Per annum
•	Floor Area: 255.21sqm*
•       Potential GFA: 363.75sqm*
•	Situated in the heart of Manly Corso amongst market leading retailers
•	Servicing 8 million visitors annually walking from the ferry to Manly Beach
•	Fantastic accessibility; moments from council car parks, bus and ferry services to Sydney CBD, North Sydney and the greater Northern Beaches

CBRE as the exclusive selling agent, is pleased to present Suite 1, 18 Sydney Road, Manly. The property is a premium office suite comprising a large open plan office with a floor area of 353sqm* and six (6) secure car spaces. Situated on the doorstep of Manly’s pedestrian arcade on Sydney Road, the office suite provides a modern high-end practical fitout, sleek kitchenette and employee break out area, two generous enclosed offices or meeting rooms, male and female amenities, and an inviting reception area.

Suite 1, 18 Sydney Road is ideal for an owner occupier looking to operate from the space and take advantage of the extraordinary lifestyle that Manly has to offer including proximity to popular bars, cafés, restaurants, shops and Manly Beach, whilst being only a 20* minute ferry ride to Sydney’s CBD. Additionally, the property provides an outstanding investment opportunity that can capitalise off Manly’s high demand leasing market.

Suite 1, 18 Sydney Road, Manly capitalises on the following key attributes:

-Large 353sqm* of prime office suite
-Presented with an extremely rare six (6) secure car spaces in the centre of Manly 
-Offered with vacant possession, ideal for owner occupiers 
-On the doorstep of Manly’s popular pedestrian arcade ‘The Corso’
-Metres from the world-renowned Manly Beach, voted Australia’ best beach in TripAdvisor 2019 Travellers’ Choice Awards
-Lifestyle focussed locality in proximity to vibrant cafés, bars, restaurants, and retail.  
-Fantastic accessibility only moments from Manly Wharf with direct services to Sydney CBD
- A modern high-end practical fitout, sleek kitchenette and employee break out area, two generous enclosed offices or meeting rooms, male and female amenities, and an inviting reception area.
-Ideal for both owner occupiers and investors 

Suite 1, 18 Sydney Road, Manly will be sold via an online Public Auction on Tuesday 28th of September 2021 at 10.30am at AuctionWORKS (live stream & online bidding available).
